The paper discusses a machine learning approach to improve the performance of a widely deployed technique for testing programs, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The focus on identifying security flaws suggests a potential fit with the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of adaptive learning and probability distributions suggests a potential fit with the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of program instrumentation and code coverage suggests a potential fit with the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Finally, the use of bandit-based optimization suggests a potential fit with the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
